  <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 dark:text-white">
    <header class="masthead bg-cover" style="background-image: url(<%=image_url('guitar_player.png')%>)">
      <div class="site-heading">
        <h1 class="font-outline-2">Chord Switching</h1>
        <span class="subheading">Improve your speed and accuracy when playing guitar</span>
      </div>
    </header>
    <article class="pb-10">
      <p>Perhaps the best technique to improve your guitar playing is to develop clean, crisp and speedy chord changes.
        The best way to do this is by using the "1 minute switch" technique.
      </p>
        
      <figure class="max-w-screen-md mx-auto text-center">
        <svg class="w-10 h-10 mx-auto mb-3 text-gray-400 dark:text-gray-600" aria-hidden="true" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 18 14">
          <path d="M6 0H2a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v4a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h4v1a3 3 0 0 1-3 3H2a1 1 0 0 0 0 2h1a5.006 5.006 0 0 0 5-5V2a2 2 0 0 0-2-2Zm10 0h-4a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v4a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h4v1a3 3 0 0 1-3 3h-1a1 1 0 0 0 0 2h1a5.006 5.006 0 0 0 5-5V2a2 2 0 0 0-2-2Z"/>
        </svg>
        <blockquote>
          <p class="text-2xl italic font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
          "The concept is simple: time yourself for one minute and see how many changes
          between two chords you can do in that time. This works better than any other method
          I have ever heard of for developing your chord change skills. It's really quite
          astounding how well this trick works."
          </p>
        </blockquote>
        <figcaption class="flex items-center justify-center mt-6 space-x-3 rtl:space-x-reverse">
          <div class="flex items-center divide-x-2 rtl:divide-x-reverse divide-gray-500 dark:divide-gray-700">
            <cite class="pe-3 font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Justin Guitar</cite>
            <cite class="ps-3 text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
              <a href="https://www.justinguitar.com/guitar-lessons/one-minute-changes-exercise-b1-110" class="font-medium text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-500 hover:underline">1 Minute Changes</a>
            </cite>
          </div>
        </figcaption>
      </figure>
      <p class="mt-10">
      This site will take the tedium out of tracking your progress in your 1 minute chord switch practices. It will:
      </p>
      <ul class="ps-10 list-disc">
        <li>Keep track of the chords you know</li>
        <li>Set up practices of any duration to run switches between random chords you know</li>
        <li>Track the results of your practices and help you chart your progress over time</li>
      </ul>
      <h2 class="text-xl mt-10">How it works</h2>
      <p>
        Use the <a href="/chords" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-500 hover:underline">Chords</a> section to track the chords you have learned. Then use the
        <a href="/sessions" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-500 hover:underline">Practice</a> section to start chord switch practice sessions. Finally, track
        your progess using the <a href="/progress" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-500 hover:underline">Progress</a> section of the site.
      </p>
